  <compounddef id="group__tlc5971__interface" kind="group">
    <compoundname>tlc5971_interface</compoundname>
    <title>TLC5971</title>
    <innerfile refid="tlc5971_8h">tlc5971.h</innerfile>
    <sectiondef kind="func">
      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__tlc5971__interface_1gacc0ab1f6ae658de98d043e49291abea4" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>int</type>
        <definition>int tlc5971_set_global_brightness</definition>
        <argsstring>(const struct device *dev, struct led_rgb pixel)</argsstring>
        <name>tlc5971_set_global_brightness</name>
        <param>
          <type>const struct <ref refid="structdevice" kindref="compound">device</ref> *</type>
          <declname>dev</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>struct <ref refid="structled__rgb" kindref="compound">led_rgb</ref></type>
          <declname>pixel</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Set the global brightness control (BC) levels of a TLC5971 strip. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The TLC5971 has a 7-bit global brightness control (BC) for each color group (Red, Green, Blue). This function allows setting these values.</para>
<para>The brightness value of each channel of <computeroutput>pixel</computeroutput> (r, g, b) maps to the corresponding global brightness control register (BCR, BCG, BCB) and must be lower than or equal to <ref refid="group__tlc5971__interface_1gaee75c4832a72869ca6e2960c726ed707" kindref="member">TLC5971_GLOBAL_BRIGHTNESS_CONTROL_MAX</ref>.</para>
<para>The change takes effect on the next update of the LED strip.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>dev</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>LED strip device </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>pixel</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Global brightness values for RGB channels</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>0 on success, negative on error </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
